Lab:SQL injection UNION attack, retrieving data from other tables

This was another UNION attack where we used simple queries first to determine the number of columns and the datatype they are using.
I quickly did that and found out it has two columns with string datatype and surely they had username and password since i was supposed to gather data around it to login as admin.
I quickly built up a query injection to take out that data
and as you can see in image it was a success.
I logged in as admin and it worked out well.

Payload used:'+UNION+SELECT+username,+password+FROM+users--

Steps to reproduce:
1.Perform a sorting and capture the request and send it to repeater
2.Enter the basic single NULL payload in category parameter
4.Keep adding NULL values until you receive an OK response
4.Now change the NULL values one by one with string or the datatype 
whose column you are looking for
5.We keep doing it for string and found out the first and second column has it.
6.We used a query with username and password to extract that data from the table users 


